      <title>Re: Pathing Update</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&amp;message.id=12449#M12449</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;After trying to both /bug and /petition for the awful pathing regarding pets in pretty much all OOW zones (Pet would get stuck between pathing nodes while trying to chase mobs, running back and forth 50 times like mobs do on bridges in Karnors) I was redirected to this forum and also this specific topic. I should note that it took me 2 petitions as the initial petition got nothing more than a bot auto reply/close saying I should search the KB *shrug*. (Why are the only human GMs from Stormhammer?)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In any case... I've been toying with pathing in test programs for a couple days now to hopefully assist you with this problem. I also wanted to improve current movement behaviour by smoothing out the path followed by NPCs. For as long as EQ has been running... every single NPC has always been attracted to pathing like a magnet, turning around instantly at corners etc etc which is hardly realistic. So I came up with this solution:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" href="http://x.lanfanatics.nl/fluent.html"&gt;Fluent Pathing&lt;/a&gt; (animated javascript)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I dont know if it can be implemented due to cpu budgets and such, but on my system it dont seem to have much effect on CPU usage (about 2-4%) and this is javascript, far from optimized and nowhere near the performance of C/C++ so it can only get faster.</description>
