      <title>Re: Pathing Update</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&amp;message.id=12406#M12406</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I spent a &lt;A href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;amp;message.id=212047" target=_blank&gt;tremendous amount of time hunting Tanglefeet mobs in Arcstone&lt;/A&gt;.&amp;nbsp; During that, I noticed some serious warping/pathing issues which I will try my best to describe.&amp;nbsp; This is very reproducible, so it might be a good place to run some tests:&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;If you approach the Tanglefoot area from the Arcstone side, the ramp to Relic will be on your left, the falloff to Freeport on your right.&amp;nbsp; As you first approach the Tanglefeet, there will be two static mobs in front of you and a third roamer will approach from the left.&amp;nbsp; Staying back from these mobs is where you set up camp.&amp;nbsp; On your left is a sheer cliff wall going up.&amp;nbsp; Label this Cliff-A.&amp;nbsp; You can climb this cliff but its steep and slow.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;If you go out past these three mobs, hugging the wall on your left, you can pull other tanglefeet to your camp.&amp;nbsp; At this point, the terrain has eased up and you can head higher if you want.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;If you stay high up on this wall and pull a tanglefoot, it will instantly warp to the cliff wall.&amp;nbsp; Now, to avoid adds, try pulling your target UP the hill and then run back toward your camp along the top of the ledge (on even elevation with the Relic platform) then jump down Cliff-A to your group.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The warp happens as you pull your mob up the hill and more importantly when you run to Cliff-A.&amp;nbsp; Your mob warps instantly to Cliff-A (and is there before you are) every time.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Give it a try.&amp;nbsp; Its a good way to test some pathing issues with elevations changes.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</description>
