      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;Grum,&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Are these pathing bugs the same ones that are affecting arrows not hitting mobs that are up against an object or wall?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I've got a large thread going in the Veteran's forums that details this bug/exploit if you get a moment to check it out.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It is a bug/exploit that is repeatable.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To test it you can go to the Freeport Militia House in East Freeport.  Outside of the door to the Militia House are two guards.  If you stand in front of them and hit Ranged Attack, your arrows will not hit them.  You don't register a miss or anything, simply nothing happens to them, you just keep firing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If you do not move from that original location and cast a spell on one of them to aggro him, as soon as he steps forward all of the arrows that should have been hitting him, will register a hit all at once.  If you move even the slightest bit from your original location no hits at all will register when the guard moves.  It is important to note that these invisible arrows that don't register actually create an invisible wall that other players cannot even walk through.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;There are many examples listed and locations given in the thread on the Veteran's board.  Thread is titled &amp;quot;UPDATE to the bug with arrows not hitting mobs?&amp;quot;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I would give you a link, but I don't have that capability yet.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Thank you.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
